  Attorney Ronald Machen told House Speaker John Boehner that former IRS official Lois Lerner could not be charged with a crime for refusing to testify at a 2013 congressional hearing . 
  Lerner insisted on her innocence in an opening statement but then refused to answer questions . 
  The Obama administration says she was within her rights to take the Fifth in the hearing . 
  The IRS was accused of targeting conservative nonprofit groups with extra scrutiny . 
  Lerner refused to testify voluntarily and was subpoenaed by the House Oversight Committee . 
  Machen said in a letter to Boehner that she was not guilty of a crime . 
 